{
  "$comment_schema": "Cross-impl golden vectors for the Pages Tag + HasProperty filter primitives (#1908 slice 2 increment c; #1913 ordered/LIKE predicates). Shape: { rows[], scenarios[] }. Each row is a page carrying a set of tags and a list of typed properties; scenarios apply an AND-composed list of FilterPrimitive wire objects and assert the SET of matching page ids. Only the matching-id set is compared cross-impl (representation-stable). Asserted by BOTH src-tauri/src/commands/tests/pages_tag_property_conformance_tests.rs (real query path) and src/lib/tauri-mock/__tests__/tag-property-conformance.test.ts (mock metaRowMatchesFilter / hasPropertyMatches).",
  "$comment_scope": "Covers Tag plus the full HasProperty predicate matrix the mock now implements: Exists, NotExists, Eq, Ne, Lt, Gt, Lte, Gte, Contains, StartsWith — across all four value types (Text→value_text, Ref→value_ref, Num→value_num, Date→value_date). Ordered compares numeric on value_num and lexical otherwise; Contains/StartsWith are ASCII-case-insensitive literal substring/prefix tests (SQLite LIKE is ASCII-case-insensitive and escape_like makes the needle literal) and short-circuit to no-match on a Num comparand (a numeric column has no substring). Tag reads block_tags (mock: blockTags map); HasProperty reads block_properties (mock: properties map).",
  "$comment_seeding": "Both impls seed mock/db state directly (no canonical fixtures). Rust: block_tags rows reference tag blocks (block_type='tag'), block_properties Ref values reference a real target block — both inserted via INSERT OR IGNORE before the join row, because foreign_keys=ON; Num→value_num (REAL), Date→value_date (TEXT). Mock: blockTags.set(id, Set(tags)) and properties.set(id, Map(key -> {value_text|value_ref|value_num|value_date})), cleared per scenario. Num values are small exact integers and Date values are identically-formatted YYYY-MM-DD so numeric/lexical compares agree across SQLite and JS.",
